<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-08-06T18:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-08-06T18:45:00-05:00" n="420" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d420">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/3128: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-08-06T18:00:00-05:45"><hi rend="italic">August 6,
                                        1924—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 7—11:05
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>158. My August 6, 3 p.m. After a conversation with the Minister for
                            Foreign Affairs I am authorized to inform the Department that <pb facs="0588" n="494" xml:id="pg_494"/> a definite rejection of the
                            proposed supervision is not intended. The intention is only
                            provisionally to withhold acceptance of the Department’s suggestion.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>